A simple to-do list application to run on local host
    - implements a log-in page with authentication and an add-user page
    - uses sessions for each user
    - stores user's to-do list state (i.e. complete and incomplete tasks, along with their timestamp)
        - loads the state upon login and stores upon logout
    - creates a log file for each change a user makes to a task (along with the timestamp)
    - implements dark/light mode
    - implements effects for add/removing tasks
